Beat butter and Equal(r) on medium speed of electric mixer until light and fluffy. Beat in egg and vanilla until well combined. Stir in combined 1 cup crushed cereal, flour, baking powder and salt until well blended. Stir in chocolate chips. Shape dough into balls using rounded measuring teaspoons. Roll in remaining 1/2 cup crushed cereal. Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake in preheated 375 degrees F oven 8 to 10 minutes. Remove from baking sheet and cool completely on wire rack.